# Fluff Date: 2026-02-10 14:00:04
overview:<p>The Bruin is an eighty-ton Clan-technology assault BattleMech produced by Bergan Industries C-Division on Alshain for the Ghost Bear Dominion. Introduced in 3081, the design emerged as part of the post-Jihad industrial recovery that saw the Dominion's factories resume full BattleMech production. The Bruin continues the lineage of Bergan C-Division designs that began with the Ursus in 3059 and continued with the Arcas in 3061, representing Khan Bjorn Jorgensson's vision of Inner Sphere-manufactured Clan BattleMechs.</p><p>Specifically designed to fill an assault-weight role emphasizing both mobility and psychological impact, the Bruin combines the firepower expected of an assault 'Mech with agility unusual for its weight class. Production ramped up more slowly than previous Bergan C-Division designs, but warriors who received the Bruin reported extremely positive results in the field.</p>

capabilities:<p>The Bergan-C team designed the Bruin around the concept of high mobility for an eighty-ton assault 'Mech. A 320-rated extra-light fusion engine propels the chassis to a top speed of 64 kph, while leg-mounted Clan Standard Type A3 jump jets provide 120 meters of jump capability, enabling the design to navigate even the most difficult terrain. This combination of speed and agility is unusual for an assault-class chassis and gives the Bruin tactical flexibility that many heavier designs simply cannot match.</p><p>The weapons loadout was carefully selected to provide effective firepower at all engagement ranges. An Omega 12-coil Gauss rifle and Type X "Short Bow" LRM-10 launcher deliver consistent long-range damage, while a Kolibri Delta Series large pulse laser adds devastating intermediate-range firepower. At shorter distances, a pair of Series 2f extended-range medium lasers and twin Smartshot Mark V Streak SRM-4 launchers ensure the Bruin can punish any opponent that closes to knife-fighting range. The long-range missile system, while old by Clan standards, remains one of the most compact yet reliable systems in the arsenal.</p><p>Fifteen tons of Compound 12A1 standard armor sheathes the Bruin in a protective shell befitting an assault 'Mech. With ample tonnage devoted to both survivability and firepower, the Bruin is built to absorb significant punishment while delivering sustained damage across all engagement ranges.</p>

deployment:<p>The base configuration combines long-range precision with close-quarters lethality. The Omega 12-coil Gauss rifle serves as the primary weapon, delivering devastating kinetic strikes at extreme range without generating waste heat. A Type X "Short Bow" LRM-10 launcher supplements this long-range capability, while the Kolibri Delta Series large pulse laser bridges the gap between ranged bombardment and close combat. Twin extended-range medium lasers and a pair of Streak SRM-4 launchers ensure the Bruin remains dangerous at any distance, allowing MechWarriors to engage targets effectively regardless of range bracket.</p>

history:<p>The Bruin's origins trace to the broader industrial vision of Khan Bjorn Jorgensson, who sought to produce Clan-technology BattleMechs within the Inner Sphere using the combined resources of the Ghost Bear Dominion. This initiative began in 3059 with the release of the Ursus, which demonstrated that the shattered industrial sectors of the former Free Rasalhague Republic could be revitalized for Clan military production. The integration of engineering and military leaders from Rasalhague's population played a crucial role in changing attitudes toward the Ghost Bears, shifting perceptions from invading overlords to future leaders for billions of former Rasalhaguians.</p><p>Military industrial growth continued through the 3060s, with the Arcas becoming the second successful BattleMech design upon its release in 3061. If not for the chaos of the FedCom Civil War and the devastating destruction of the Jihad, Bergan Industries' C-Division would likely have produced an entire range of Clan BattleMechs for use by Ghost Bear warriors and the absorbed Royal KungsArmé far sooner. As the widespread destruction of the Jihad wound down, the factories of the Ghost Bear Dominion resumed production, and the Bruin was the next design scheduled for completion and re-launch from the facilities on Alshain.</p><p>By 3086, the Bruin was being dispersed among second-line units throughout the Dominion. While not produced as rapidly as the earlier Arcas or Ursus designs, the Ghost Bears anticipated having a substantial number of Bruins in the field within a few years of introduction. Initial responses from assigned warriors were extremely positive, validating the design team's approach of combining assault-class firepower with unusual mobility.</p><p>The sheer size and menace of the Bruin has served the defense of the Dominion nearly as effectively as its raw firepower and combat capabilities. Raiding units that encounter Stars of pristine Ghost Bear assault 'Mechs are quick to abandon their plans and retreat. Even in an age where wholesale destruction can rain from the skies, the psychological impact of enormous BattleMechs towering over the battlefield remains a potent factor in Dominion defensive doctrine.</p>

